# 📱 Universal Tracker — Product Requirements Document (PRD v1.1)

---

# 1. Product Overview

**Universal Tracker** is a local-first Android application that allows users to define custom trackers and log structured or semi-structured data over time, with powerful visualization and statistical analysis.

It is designed as a **serious tracking tool**, not a habit or gamification app.

### Core Principles
- No accounts, no subscriptions
- No gamification or behavioral pressure
- Full user control over data
- Flexible schema with structured insights
- Fast, reliable, and offline-first

---

# 2. Core Value Proposition

Users can:
- Track anything (numeric, duration, text, or combinations)
- Define structured multi-field trackers
- Log entries quickly with precision
- Visualize trends and statistics
- Export and own their data completely

---

# 3. Product Philosophy

- Users are competent; avoid hand-holding
- Logging should be fast but deliberate
- Data should remain interpretable and consistent
- Insights should be visible but not intrusive
- Flexibility is prioritized over rigid workflows

---

# 4. Onboarding Experience (First Launch Only)

## Purpose
- Explain the app clearly
- Reduce confusion from flexibility
- Teach Tracker → Entry model
- Help create first tracker

## Flow

### Screen 1 — Introduction
- Title: “Track anything”
- Subtitle: “No rules. No pressure.”

### Screen 2 — How It Works
- Tracker → Entries → Charts visual

### Screen 3 — Capabilities
- Charts
- Statistics
- Multi-field tracking
- Reminders

### Screen 4 — Create First Tracker
- Templates (optional)
- Create from scratch

## UX Requirements
- Smooth transitions
- Subtle animations
- Optional sound (globally disable-able)

